Apple could offer at least six different <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/iphone/">iPhone</a> models in 2027, according to a proven leaker on Weibo.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/05/iPhone-18-Punch-Hole-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1003690" /><br/>
According to a post from the leaker known as "<a href="https://weibo.com/u/5143897135">Instant Digital</a>," there may be at least six new &zwnj;iPhone&zwnj; models to choose from in 2027. From the unveiling of the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-18/">iPhone 18</a> and &zwnj;iPhone&zwnj; 18e in the first half of 2027 until the fall announcement of the first &zwnj;iPhone&zwnj; 19 models, the lineup could look like this:<br/>
<br/>
